---
import Base from '../layouts/Base.astro';
import Header from '../components/Header.astro';
import Footer from '../components/Footer.astro';
---

<Base title="Support" description="Get help with Clarissa - FAQ, troubleshooting, and contact information">
  <Header />
  <main class="container support-page">
    <h1 class="gradient-text">Support</h1>
    <p class="subtitle">Get help with Clarissa</p>

    <section class="faq">
      <h2>Frequently Asked Questions</h2>

      <div class="faq-item">
        <h3>Does Clarissa require an internet connection?</h3>
        <p>
          On iOS 26+ with Apple Intelligence, Clarissa works completely offline using on-device AI. 
          For the CLI version or if you configure a cloud provider, an internet connection is required 
          for AI responses.
        </p>
      </div>

      <div class="faq-item">
        <h3>What permissions does the iOS app need?</h3>
        <p>
          Clarissa requests permissions only when you use specific features:
        </p>
        <ul>
          <li><strong>Calendar</strong> — Required to create or view calendar events</li>
          <li><strong>Contacts</strong> — Required to search or view contacts</li>
        </ul>
        <p>You can use Clarissa without granting these permissions.</p>
      </div>

      <div class="faq-item">
        <h3>How do I get an OpenRouter API key?</h3>
        <p>
          Visit <a href="https://openrouter.ai/keys" target="_blank" rel="noopener">openrouter.ai/keys</a> 
          to create a free account and generate an API key. OpenRouter provides access to Claude, GPT-4, 
          Gemini, and many other models.
        </p>
      </div>

      <div class="faq-item">
        <h3>Why isn't on-device AI working?</h3>
        <p>
          On-device AI using Apple Foundation Models requires:
        </p>
        <ul>
          <li>iOS 26+ or macOS 26+</li>
          <li>Apple Intelligence enabled in Settings</li>
          <li>A device with Apple Silicon (iPhone 15 Pro or later, M-series Macs)</li>
        </ul>
        <p>If unavailable, configure an OpenRouter API key in Settings as a fallback.</p>
      </div>

      <div class="faq-item">
        <h3>How do I clear my conversation history?</h3>
        <p>
          <strong>iOS:</strong> Tap the menu icon and select "New Conversation" or use "Clear Conversation" 
          in the menu.<br />
          <strong>CLI:</strong> Use the <code>/clear</code> command or start a new session.
        </p>
      </div>

      <div class="faq-item">
        <h3>Is Clarissa free?</h3>
        <p>
          Yes, Clarissa is free and open source. On iOS 26+, you can use it entirely for free with 
          on-device AI. Cloud providers like OpenRouter may have usage costs based on their pricing.
        </p>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section class="contact">
      <h2>Get Help</h2>
      
      <div class="contact-options">
        <a href="https://github.com/cameronrye/clarissa/issues" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="contact-card">
          <h3>Report a Bug</h3>
          <p>Found a problem? Open an issue on GitHub.</p>
        </a>

        <a href="https://github.com/cameronrye/clarissa/discussions" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="contact-card">
          <h3>Ask a Question</h3>
          <p>Have a question? Start a discussion on GitHub.</p>
        </a>

        <a href="mailto:cameron@rye.dev" class="contact-card">
          <h3>Contact Developer</h3>
          <p>Reach out directly to Cameron Rye.</p>
        </a>
      </div>
    </section>
  </main>
  <Footer />
</Base>

<style>
  .support-page {
    max-width: 800px;
    padding: 3rem 1.5rem;
  }

  h1 {
    font-size: 2.5rem;
    margin-bottom: 0.5rem;
  }

  .subtitle {
    color: var(--color-text-muted);
    font-size: 1.125rem;
    margin-bottom: 3rem;
  }

  section {
    margin-bottom: 3rem;
  }

  h2 {
    font-size: 1.5rem;
    margin-bottom: 1.5rem;
    color: var(--color-text);
  }

  .faq-item {
    margin-bottom: 2rem;
    padding-bottom: 2rem;
    border-bottom: 1px solid var(--color-border);
  }

  .faq-item:last-child {
    border-bottom: none;
  }

  .faq-item h3 {
    font-size: 1.125rem;
    margin-bottom: 0.75rem;
    color: var(--color-text);
  }

  .faq-item p, .faq-item li {
    color: var(--color-text-muted);
    line-height: 1.7;
    margin-bottom: 0.75rem;
  }

  .faq-item ul {
    padding-left: 1.5rem;
    margin: 0.75rem 0;
  }

  .faq-item code {
    background: var(--color-bg-secondary);
    padding: 0.2rem 0.5rem;
    border-radius: 4px;
    font-size: 0.875rem;
  }

  a {
    color: var(--color-cyan);
  }

  .contact-options {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: repeat(auto-fit, minmax(200px, 1fr));
    gap: 1rem;
  }

  .contact-card {
    display: block;
    padding: 1.5rem;
    background: var(--color-bg-secondary);
    border: 1px solid var(--color-border);
    border-radius: 12px;
    transition: border-color 0.2s, transform 0.2s;
    text-decoration: none;
  }

  .contact-card:hover {
    border-color: var(--color-cyan);
    transform: translateY(-2px);
  }

  .contact-card h3 {
    font-size: 1rem;
    color: var(--color-text);
    margin-bottom: 0.5rem;
  }

  .contact-card p {
    font-size: 0.875rem;
    color: var(--color-text-muted);
    margin: 0;
  }
</style>

